Alembic Configuration For Craftmeet

Alembic is the database configuration tool for this application.
It handles initial table creation, and all subsequent migrations.

It is already pre-configured to automatically update the database tables and columns 
following the existing sqlalchemy models defined in the codebase.

Usage

1. Generate the starting schema: alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Inital Migration"
2. To generate following migrations: alembic revision --autogenerate -m <Message>
3. To undo/revert migrations: alembic downgrade <number>
4. To undo/revert all migrations: alembic downgrade base
5. To migrate to the latest revision: alembic upgrade head
6. To view all migration history: alembic history --verbose
7. To view one migration history: alembic show <revision id>

Nuclear Usage

To permenantely delete specific revisions and alter the migration history,
follow these steps.

1. Revert all migrations: alembic downgrade base
2. Delete the folder from alembic/versions
3. Recreate the new revision now: alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Initial Migration"
4. Run the migration: alembic upgrade head
